    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2008-12-10</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2008-12-24T20:56:05Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>College Football Playoff Act of 2008 - Prohibits promoting, marketing, or advertising a post-season National Collegiate Athletic Association (NCAA) Division Football Bowl Subdivision (FBS) game as a championship or national championship game (or any merchandise that refers to the game as a championship or national championship game) unless such game is the final game of a single elimination post-season playoff system for which all NCAA Division I FBS conferences and unaffiliated Division I FBS teams are eligible.</p><p>Treats a violation as an unfair or deceptive act or practice under the Federal Trade Commission Act. </p><p>Makes this Act applicable to any game that occurs after January 31, 2011.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
    <title>College Football Playoff Act of 2008</title>
